\f0\fs24 \cf0 1) BC Logo is clickable. Goes to a nice screen \ which manages sites, gives global info, etc.\ \ 2) Site Name is clickable, goes to a screen that \ gives a nice overview of stuff that can be done \ in the site UI.\ \ 3) User Panel has links such as logout, link to \ profile, etc.\ \ 4) Site Panel has help screen, live search, and \ other Bottlecap-specific global options.\ \ 5) Navigation crumbs (discussed elsewhere) \ make quick navigation a breeze.\ \ 6) Subsite Links (aka context links) allow \ major parts of a subsite (e.g. Blog/Wiki in a \ "Project" to have a sticky kind of nav, on a \ per-site, per-context basis. The actual links \ are not part of Bottlecap but are custom/dynamic.\ \ 7) Site Links...ditto. Not part of Bottlecap, but \ are custom. But these are always the same, \ unlike Subsite Links which change based on \ where you are.\ \ 8) Page Title just says we might have some \ standard slots in the content area.}

\f0\fs24 \cf0 1) Note: the triangle pointed end shouldn't have \ the left border/line.\ \ 2) Underneath the Site, show the hierarchy to \ the current resource.\ \ 3) Each crumb has two modes of activation:\ \ - Open (clicking the hyperlink)\ \ - Popup (clicking anywhere else in the crumb)\ \ 4) The down-arrow for the popup only appears \ on hover.\ \ 5) This pattern appears in lots of places, e.g. \ the User Menu. Goal is to eliminate screen \ redraws and loss of context.\ \ 6) The panel that appears is the width of the \ content area, and one-half the height. Like \ other dialogs, it closes when you click the \ same thing you did to open, or click outside \ the panel, or hit escape.}
